description.narrative: The proposed new PDO is: to assist targeted vulnerable urban populations in the Recipient’s territory to (i) increase their incomesthrough the provision of short term employment; (ii) improve their knowledge, experience and basic employment skills that are valued in the workplace and society; and (iii) improve their access to services and markets through repaired, more climate resilient roads and access infrastructure.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section IA and IB | Description :Throughout implementation, the Recipient shall maintain the ProjectSteering Committee and the Technical Coordination Committee | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section IE | Description :The Recipient shall carry out the Project in accordance with theEnvironmental and Social Management Guidelines. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2. Section 1 A | Description :The Recipient shall establish and thereafter maintain the ProjectSteering Committee with functions and composition satisfactory tothe Bank. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2. Section 1 B | Description :The Recipient shall establish and thereafter maintain the TechnicalCoordination Committee with functions and composition satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2. Section 1 D | Description :The Recipient shall prepare an Administrative, Financial and AccountingManual acceptable to the Bank for both MID and HCC. | Due Date :31-Jul-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2. Section 2 A & B | Description :The recipient shall monitor and evaluate the progress of the Projectand prepare Quarterly Project Reports (including IFRs) to be submitted within 45 days of the end of each quarter | Frequency:Quarterly
